<div id="review_2339570634" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2339570634" />
    <a title="Gavin Haughton" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/73980557-gavin-haughton"><img alt="Gavin Haughton" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1511091776p2/73980557.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2339570634?book_show_action=true">Jun 03, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Gavin Haughton" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Gavin Haughton" href="/user/show/73980557-gavin-haughton">Gavin Haughton</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2339570634" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer563783233939611255">Very interesting and insightful book. Reading the view of a soldier during the conquest of Mexico from first discovering the land and being defeated on its beaches, to returning with an army and Cortes, and finally the battle to take Mexico City. The author talks in detail about the battles, but most interesting to me, all the other things, descriptions of their food, customs, houses, different provinces and their cultures. It mentions small jokes, funny happenings, and personalities that are of</span>
  <span id="freeText563783233939611255" style="display:none">Very interesting and insightful book. Reading the view of a soldier during the conquest of Mexico from first discovering the land and being defeated on its beaches, to returning with an army and Cortes, and finally the battle to take Mexico City. The author talks in detail about the battles, but most interesting to me, all the other things, descriptions of their food, customs, houses, different provinces and their cultures. It mentions small jokes, funny happenings, and personalities that are often missed in documentaries or films. This wasn't particularly a topic I was interested in before, but after reading this first-person account, I feel like I have opened a door into a large part of history I knew very little about. The written style is very easy to read, accessible for everyone.</span>
  <a data-text-id="563783233939611255" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
